Instructional design principles:
- 4-hour workshop = 4 focused modules
- Each module buildable in isolation
- Time boxes prevent rabbit holes
- Mix of theory (20%) and hands-on (80%)

Module 1 structure reasoning:
- Environment setup first to catch issues early
- Conceptual foundation before coding
- Quick win with calculator agent
- Backup plans for common failures

Content considerations:
- Academic papers provide depth for advanced students
- Common issues section based on pilot workshop feedback
- Platform-specific solutions from real testing
- Instructor notes capture tacit knowledge

Directory structure supports:
- Instructor-led presentation (slides/)
- Self-paced learning (exercises/, solutions/)
- Automated validation (tests/)
